===========================================================================================

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

name: standard hub dirs and permissions

The top-level /efs should be owned by root but traversible and readable by all:

$ show_dir /efs
drwxr-xr-x. root root /efs

All of the top-level subdirs should be owned by root and exposed for reading and execution to 'other'.
Note that since the group ownership is root those perms are essentially ignored.

$ show_dir /efs/*
drwxr-xr-x. root root /efs/backups

$ cd /efs
$ ls
backups
data
services
teams
test-specs
users

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
name: teams directory and team subdirs

The teams directory itself must be owned by root:root
The teams directory itself must provide only read and execute
permissions to 'other' which basically services everyone but root:

$ show_dir /efs/teams
drwxr-xr-x. root root /efs/teams

Ensure the admin and members are treated as grownups (group w), new files and
directories are created with the same group by default (setgid s), and team
members cannot move or delete each others files (sticky bit T):

$ ls -lt /efs/teams | grep -v -E 'drwxrws--T|total'
exit_code: fail

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
name: users directory and subdirs

$ show_dir /efs/users
drwxr-xr-x. root root /efs/users

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
name: services directory and subdirs

$ show_dir /efs/services
drwxr-xr-x. root root /efs/services

$ show_dir /efs/services/announcements
drwxr-xr-x. root root /efs/services/announcements

$ show_dir /efs/services/efs-quota
drwxr-xr-x. root root /efs/services/efs-quota

$ show_dir /efs/services/uidgid
drwxr-xr-x. root root /efs/services/uidgid

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
name: data directory and subdirs

$ show_dir /efs/data
drwxr-xr-x. root root /efs/data

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
name: backups directory and subdirs

$ show_dir /efs/backups
drwxr-xr-x. root root /efs/backups

$ show_dir /efs/backups/uidgid
drwxr-xr-x. root root /efs/backups/uidgid

